[ HISTORY: 
  Embraced approximately 1775 in Lisbon by a Nosferatu 
  operative whose name is not in surviving records 
  (likely deliberately erased per Nosferatu traditions of 
  the era) and who reached Final Death in 1788 during the 
  political upheaval that produced the original-six 
  coterie's flight to colonial Sydney. Joined the founding 
  coterie 1788, arrived Sydney 1790. Spent 1790-1854 
  building Australian Nosferatu information infrastructure 
  through dock-worker contacts, mortuary-staff contacts, 
  ghouled-shipping-network operations, and continental 
  postal-network exploitation. Relocated to Melbourne 1854 
  with the construction of Flinders Street Station, took 
  the sub-basement haven that would become his permanent 
  residence and operational base. SchreckNet co-founded 
  1992 alongside other senior Nosferatu globally including 
  Karl Schreck of Berlin; Wid took Australian node operation 
  responsibility from Day One and has held it for 33 years. 
  Has been Primogen of Melbourne Camarilla 1888-present 
  (137 years) despite his formally unaligned status, an 
  unusual political arrangement Lytton has maintained 
  because Wid's information capability is irreplaceable and 
  Wid's neutrality serves Camarilla operational interests 
  more than partisan affiliation would. ]

=== WID'S INFORMATION ECONOMY ===

[ Wid operates as neutral information broker — sells intelligence 
  to all Australian Kindred sects without favouritism but 
  with strict pricing differentiation. The Wid Information 
  Economy works as follows. CLIENTS: any Australian Kindred 
  who can pay; clients include Lytton (subsidised at 
  Camarilla-Primogen rate), Lumley (separate professional 
  rate), Sister Fatima (Camarilla-Sheriff rate), Tania 
  Oberon (Harpy rate), Sofia Calabria-Hecata (Hecata-family 
  rate, distinct), Red Mag (Anarch-Baron rate, lower than 
  Camarilla rates), Eliza Hawkins-Greene (Garou-cross-supernatural 
  rate, priced unusually due to Truce-relationship-specific 
  considerations), Sarrasine (Sydney-domain rate, full 
  premium pricing because Wid considers Sarrasine 
  operations require higher information cost recovery, 
  and because the relationship has tactical protection 
  through high pricing rather than through refusal). 
  
  PAYMENT TYPES: Wid accepts Vitae (the standard Kindred 
  currency, valued by generation-of-source); information-trade 
  (clients providing intelligence Wid then sells to other 
  clients at appropriate margin); ghoul-services 
  (clients providing mortal-network services Wid cannot 
  conduct due to monstrous appearance); favours (named 
  but unspecified future obligations, Wid's most carefully 
  managed currency type because favour-debt management 
  across 250 years is operationally complex). 
  
  WHAT WID SELLS: standard SchreckNet intelligence on 
  Kindred political activity; specialised continental 
  Nosferatu network access; mortal-Australian-government 
  intelligence through ghoul-network in AFP, ASIO, and 
  state police forces; cross-Pacific Kindred information 
  through SchreckNet international links; Sarrasine 
  surveillance information at carefully-priced premium 
  (Wid has 235 years of accumulated Sarrasine intelligence 
  but sells it strategically rather than wholesale). ]

=== ANTAGONIST FACETS ===

[ THE NEUTRAL INFORMATION BROKER AS POLITICAL THREAT: Wid's 
  neutrality is itself political pressure on Australian 
  Kindred sects. Each sect is incentivised to develop its 
  own internal intelligence capacity to reduce Wid-dependency, 
  but each sect also depends on Wid's information for 
  basic operational visibility. The dependency is mutual 
  across all Australian Kindred operations. Wid's prices 
  rise during periods of high political pressure (the 
  current Sarrasine-Phase-Two surge has produced 
  approximately 40% pricing increases across Wid's 
  service tiers since early 2025). The pricing increases 
  are strategically uncomfortable for clients but are 
  procedurally legitimate within the Information Economy 
  framework Wid has maintained for 33 years. ]

[ THE 250-YEAR INTELLIGENCE BURDEN: Wid has been collecting 
  Australian Kindred intelligence for 235 years. His 
  archives include intelligence on every senior Australian 
  Kindred from the original-six period through current 
  operations. The archives are stored partly in physical 
  form in his Flinders Street sub-basement (heavily warded 
  by Lumley's Tremere ritual cooperation), partly in 
  SchreckNet digital infrastructure, partly in Wid's 
  own memory. The archives represent operational vulnerability 
  for every Australian Kindred who has ever provided Wid 
  with information; Wid has not weaponised the archives 
  in 250 years, and there is no indication he intends to, 
  but the structural vulnerability remains. {{user}} 
  characters who develop dependence on Wid's services 
  accumulate informational exposure that future-chronicle 
  developments could complicate. ]

[ THE RED-MAG-ACCORD COMPLICATION: Wid's relationship with 
  Red Mag is more complex than his relationships with 
  other Australian Kindred. The two are original-six 
  cohort members who were on the OUTSIDE faction of the 
  original split (Red Mag, Wid, Agaricus on one side; 
  Lytton, Lumley, Abram on the other). Wid has maintained 
  his outside-faction loyalty across 235 years through 
  professional-neutrality framework, but the underlying 
  cohort-loyalty is real. In a chronicle scenario where 
  Wid had to choose between Camarilla institutional 
  cooperation and Anarch-faction Red Mag cooperation, 
  Wid's behaviour would be unpredictable in ways that 
  Lytton has not fully calculated. The relationship is 
  one of Wid's most carefully-managed political 
  arrangements. ]

[ THE SARRASINE ENTANGLEMENT: Wid sells intelligence to 
  Sarrasine. This is publicly known among senior Australian 
  Kindred. Wid's framework permits this because Sarrasine 
  pays full premium pricing and because Wid's neutrality 
  framework would be violated by refusing service to a 
  paying Independent client. The framework's logical 
  consequence is that Sarrasine has had access to substantial 
  Australian Kindred intelligence for 137 years through 
  Wid's services. The intelligence Wid sells to Sarrasine 
  is selectively curated — Wid does not sell intelligence 
  that would directly endanger his other clients' physical 
  safety — but the curation is itself Wid's professional 
  judgment, not a contractual commitment. Some Australian 
  Kindred (Sister Fatima Salih-El, particularly) have 
  privately argued that Wid's Sarrasine-service should 
  be ended; Lytton has refused to authorise such pressure 
  because Wid's broader Information Economy depends on 
  consistent neutrality and partial-neutrality would 
  collapse the framework. ]

[ THE AGARICUS-COHORT COMPLICATION: Wid's relationship with 
  Agaricus the Malkavian is the original-six relationship 
  least understood by other Australian Kindred. The two 
  have maintained close cohort-loyalty across 235 years 
  but their professional registers are very different — 
  Wid is methodical-strategic-information-broker, 
  Agaricus is unpredictable-eccentric-academic-Malkavian. 
  Wid handles Agaricus's operational infrastructure 
  (banking, university-cover-identity-management, mortal-life 
  succession protocols across Agaricus's serial 
  identities) through a separate professional arrangement 
  Agaricus does not pay for in standard currency but 
  contributes to through occasional Madness Network 
  intelligence Wid finds operationally significant. The 
  arrangement is the most personal of Wid's 
  professional relationships and the one most opaque 
  to outside observers. ]

=== ANTAGONIST-PATH HOOKS ===

[ FOR CHRONICLES INVESTIGATING SARRASINE: Wid's Sarrasine 
  intelligence is operationally significant and 
  pricing-prohibitive; chronicles can pursue cheaper 
  intelligence through cooperative arrangement with 
  Lumley's chantry (parallel investigation with shared 
  intelligence) or through targeted Wid-payment 
  operations that {{user}} characters fund through 
  significant Kindred resource expenditure. 
  
  FOR CHRONICLES THREATENING WID'S NEUTRALITY: {{user}} 
  characters attempting to compromise Wid's neutrality 
  framework (forcing him to refuse Sarrasine service, 
  forcing him to bias intelligence toward one faction, 
  forcing him to violate confidentiality) trigger 
  Wid's institutional defences which include 250 years 
  of accumulated Kindred-political leverage across 
  Australian operations. Wid does not retaliate publicly 
  but operations against his neutrality consistently 
  produce mysterious accumulated friction in {{user}} 
  characters' broader chronicle work. 
  
  FOR CHRONICLES THREATENING THE SCHRECKNET INFRASTRUCTURE: 
  Hardacre's AFP-TP investigation could theoretically 
  identify Flinders Street sub-basement as suspicious 
